# granite4.1-30b-agent — general chat + agentic tool-use (non-CN alternate to qwen3-32b-agent)
# Base model: granite4.1:30b  (IBM, 28.9B, Q4_K_M; capabilities: completion, tools)
# Customisations: num_ctx raised (Ollama default 2048) -> 65536; base template, tools, and
#   sampling preserved.
#
#   NOTE: granite4.1 exposes NO thinking capability (verified via /api/show), so there is nothing
#   to disable — this is purely a context-raised variant. The base model ships no sampling
#   parameters, so Ollama's runtime defaults apply unless overridden below.
#
#   Why the context raise matters: Pi talks to Ollama's OpenAI-compatible /v1 endpoint, which
#   cannot pass num_ctx per request — so without this the model is pinned to the 2048 default.
#   Open WebUI uses native /api/chat and can override num_ctx in the UI, but baking it in gives
#   a single durable default across Pi + WebUI + Goose. ~26-28 GB VRAM at 65K, fits the 48 GB M4 Pro.
#
# To recreate on a fresh Ollama install:
#   ollama pull granite4.1:30b
#   ollama create granite4.1-30b-agent:latest -f granite4.1-30b-agent.Modelfile
#
# Mac Mini blob SHA (current): sha256-b33e4376e3581d11236ea53ced6b38399f6e91c0a391488486dc0827972f23f6
#
# To update a single parameter without a full recreate (e.g. num_ctx):
#   curl -s -X POST http://michaels-mac-mini.cosmach.net:11434/api/create \
#     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#     -d '{"model":"granite4.1-30b-agent:latest","from":"granite4.1-30b-agent:latest","parameters":{"num_ctx":65536}}'

FROM granite4.1:30b

PARAMETER num_ctx 65536
